track_notes: I have been there 3 times, i guess this time i was not at the real summit. I must go back to check where is the good trig poin. Anyway, it is no so easy to found the path because of it is a no mans land (except during hunting season)!

You can park at the village next to the school, or if you can use the forest road and park anywhere. The path is no easy to found and the second part is a bit surprising. You may encounter wild animals or hunters depending of your luck!

Not so easy!!! After few years the original path is not anymore! Now you must park at La Courbaisse and use a small road closed by a barrier. When you reach the col, go left and try to found the good way and go to the electrical HT pylones. Sometimes youll have to climb some easy rocks. The good summit is the last one very far.
